abstract_summ: COVID-19, a novel disease, appeared in December 2019 in China and rapidly spread across the world . High incidence (2.9/100,000) and cases fatality rates (1.7%) were observed in Pakistan . Median age of patients was 64.5 years (IQR: 54-70) with 75% (n=75) Males . 71 (71%) cases had one or more documented comorbidities at the time of diagnosis .
